Marine Toys for Tots Foundation Logo Toys for Tots is a program run by the United States Marine Corps Reserve which distributes toys to children whose parents cannot afford to buy them gifts for Christmas. The program was founded in 1947 by reservist Major Bill Hendricks. The Marine Toys for Tots Foundation, a 501 not-for-profit public charity located in Triangle, Virginia, serves to fund, raise funds for, and support the program. Source
